During the course the new conceptions and methodological approaches in neurobiology are delivered to the students. The students are responsible to pass the course of seminars in format of journal club. Moreover, the other major task of students is to participate in research performed in the field of neurobiology in the Department of Physiology.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main aim of course is to teach the students how to analyze the scientific publications in the field of neurobiology. The basic knowledge how to set up and perform scientific experiments is provided to the students attending the course.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of the course the students have to demonstrate the ability to analyze the scientific literature in neurobiology. Also they have to have the theoretical knowledge how to conduct the scientific experiments in the field of neuroscience.
